OL,3,CCarer admits neglect of resident who
OL,4,Cdied after medication mix-up
OL,6,FOn the afternoon of September 6, Mr
OL,7,FDavies became unwell, struggling to
OL,8,Fbreathe and losing consciousness.
OL,10,FBarnard called an ambulance for Mr
OL,11,FDavies but did not reveal she had
OL,12,Fgiven him morphine, and told doctors
OL,13,Fit was not possible for him to have
OL,14,Faccess to the drug.
OL,16,FTwo days later, on September 8,
OL,17,FBarnard rang Kim Jones, deputy manager
OL,18,Fof the home, to tell her she had given
OL,19,FMr Davies the wrong medication.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
